WEBVTT

00:00:00.968 --> 00:00:02.803
(Yuma)
Last time on
"Yu-Gi-Oh! Zexal":

00:00:02.803 --> 00:00:04.438
♪

00:00:04.438 --> 00:00:07.808
Where's your pal Ray, so
we can this duel started?

00:00:07.808 --> 00:00:09.276
He couldn't make it, Girag!

00:00:09.276 --> 00:00:11.478
So you'll just be losing to me!

00:00:11.478 --> 00:00:13.580
Why you little--

00:00:13.580 --> 00:00:16.517
(Ray)
Hold everything!

00:00:16.517 --> 00:00:17.985
Ray, you're here!

00:00:17.985 --> 00:00:19.353
You shouldn't have come!

00:00:19.353 --> 00:00:21.788
This Girag guy means
serious business!

00:00:21.788 --> 00:00:24.625
So then why did you decide
to come here and duel?

00:00:24.625 --> 00:00:25.826
Well--

00:00:25.826 --> 00:00:27.961
Look, I know I'm
kinda new to dueling,

00:00:27.961 --> 00:00:31.164
but I can't let you
fight my battles for me.

00:00:31.164 --> 00:00:32.599
I get ya.

00:00:32.599 --> 00:00:35.702
How about I take the
both of you on in a duel?

00:00:35.702 --> 00:00:37.971
I activate a
Barian Sphere Field!

00:00:37.971 --> 00:00:43.777
♪

00:00:43.777 --> 00:00:47.447
You're gonna pay for
messing up Alito, Ray!

00:00:47.447 --> 00:00:50.384
(yelling)

00:00:50.384 --> 00:00:53.420
Go Barian Battlemorph!

00:00:53.420 --> 00:00:56.089
♪

00:00:56.089 --> 00:01:00.193
I Xyz summon Number 106!

00:01:00.193 --> 00:01:03.797
Giant Hand!

00:01:03.797 --> 00:01:06.233
Another Number over a hundred!

00:01:06.233 --> 00:01:09.236
Giant Hand, Attack!

00:01:09.236 --> 00:01:11.238
(yelling)

00:01:11.238 --> 00:01:15.509
♪

00:01:15.509 --> 00:01:17.177
Yuma, Ray!

00:01:17.177 --> 00:01:20.113
I am not sure how
much longer I--

00:01:20.113 --> 00:01:22.115
(yelling)

00:01:22.115 --> 00:01:24.985
♪

00:01:24.985 --> 00:01:26.820
Astral!

00:01:26.820 --> 00:01:34.628
♪

00:01:34.628 --> 00:01:37.664
♪ Still together as one,
'cause divided we're none ♪

00:01:37.664 --> 00:01:40.033
♪ Ready to go,
we feel the flow ♪

00:01:40.033 --> 00:01:42.769
♪ So don't stand in our way,
you know we ain't afraid ♪

00:01:42.769 --> 00:01:45.639
♪ This is our time,
we're in control ♪

00:01:45.639 --> 00:01:48.141
♪ If I trip up today,
you just wipe it away ♪

00:01:48.141 --> 00:01:50.744
♪ All of my fears
are gone, erased ♪

00:01:50.744 --> 00:01:53.647
♪ Let us tear down the walls,
till the final night falls ♪

00:01:53.647 --> 00:01:56.316
♪ The bonds of our souls
can't be replaced ♪

00:01:56.316 --> 00:01:58.118
♪ Let us fight together ♪

00:01:58.118 --> 00:02:01.555
♪ Regret it never,
our dreams will be ♪

00:02:01.555 --> 00:02:04.091
♪ Halfway to forever ♪

00:02:04.091 --> 00:02:07.995
♪ Our light comes
shining through ♪

00:02:07.995 --> 00:02:09.396
♪ Reach down deep,
beat defeat ♪

00:02:09.396 --> 00:02:11.999
♪ Do all that we can do ♪

00:02:11.999 --> 00:02:14.635
♪ Halfway to forever ♪

00:02:14.635 --> 00:02:17.371
♪ We've got nothing to lose ♪

00:02:17.371 --> 00:02:20.073
♪ Keep breathing,
believing ♪

00:02:20.073 --> 00:02:22.509
♪ Halfway to forever ♪♪

00:02:22.509 --> 00:02:27.447
♪

00:02:31.418 --> 00:02:34.554
Astral, please...
speak to me!

00:02:34.554 --> 00:02:35.922
I am here.

00:02:35.922 --> 00:02:38.859
Yuma, I cannot keep
dueling by your side.

00:02:38.859 --> 00:02:40.193
I am very sorry.

00:02:40.193 --> 00:02:43.463
I must retreat to the
safety of the Key at once.

00:02:43.463 --> 00:02:45.332
The Sphere Field's
effects are too great

00:02:45.332 --> 00:02:47.401
for me to withstand any more--

00:02:47.401 --> 00:02:49.002
But know this my friend:

00:02:49.002 --> 00:02:51.238
I have great faith
that you can win...

00:02:51.238 --> 00:02:54.007
If you just feel the flow.

00:02:54.007 --> 00:02:55.342
♪

00:02:55.342 --> 00:02:57.411
I won't let you down.

00:02:57.411 --> 00:03:00.580
♪

00:03:00.580 --> 00:03:02.015
Just like Astral,

00:03:02.015 --> 00:03:05.318
I would say your chances
of winning have disappeared.

00:03:05.318 --> 00:03:10.323
♪

00:03:10.323 --> 00:03:11.558
What are you doing?

00:03:11.558 --> 00:03:13.593
Looks like he's
taking off his Key.

00:03:13.593 --> 00:03:15.162
Tori!

00:03:15.162 --> 00:03:16.296
Heads up!

00:03:16.296 --> 00:03:23.070
♪

00:03:23.070 --> 00:03:24.171
Yuma!

00:03:24.171 --> 00:03:25.972
Hold on to my Key for me.

00:03:25.972 --> 00:03:28.508
Please keep it safe
until we win this.

00:03:28.508 --> 00:03:30.577
And Ray, don't worry,
I'll protect you.

00:03:30.577 --> 00:03:33.046
We'll get through
this duel together.

00:03:33.046 --> 00:03:34.748
Ha, impossible!

00:03:34.748 --> 00:03:36.717
There is no way
you can fight me

00:03:36.717 --> 00:03:38.585
and keep an eye on Ray!

00:03:38.585 --> 00:03:41.655
I look forward to
watching you try and fail.

00:03:41.655 --> 00:03:43.557
♪

00:03:43.557 --> 00:03:46.126
Yuma doesn't have to
worry about me, Girag.

00:03:46.126 --> 00:03:49.029
I can take care of
myself with this!

00:03:49.029 --> 00:03:52.165
I'm summoning Shining Sly!

00:03:52.165 --> 00:03:54.968
With this card, when there's
an Xyz Monster on the field,

00:03:54.968 --> 00:03:57.237
I can't get attacked!

00:03:57.237 --> 00:03:59.072
Now Yuma can take
his mind off me

00:03:59.072 --> 00:04:00.907
and focus on you.

00:04:00.907 --> 00:04:04.544
Then I place one card
facedown and end my turn!

00:04:04.544 --> 00:04:07.714
Yuma, go ahead,
it's your move!

00:04:07.714 --> 00:04:09.015
Aww, yeah!

00:04:09.015 --> 00:04:10.150
My turn!

00:04:10.150 --> 00:04:12.385
I draw!

00:04:12.385 --> 00:04:14.688
I summon Gogogo Golem!

00:04:14.688 --> 00:04:17.491
♪

00:04:17.491 --> 00:04:19.259
Giant Hand may be
able to put a stop

00:04:19.259 --> 00:04:21.461
to my monster's
special abilities,

00:04:21.461 --> 00:04:24.631
but who needs those when
my monster's stronger!

00:04:24.631 --> 00:04:28.101
It's time to do some damage
by using Utopia and Golem

00:04:28.101 --> 00:04:30.403
as a one-two punch!

00:04:30.403 --> 00:04:32.072
Go, Utopia!

00:04:32.072 --> 00:04:34.241
Attack Giant Hand!

00:04:34.241 --> 00:04:36.076
Rising Sun Slash!

00:04:36.076 --> 00:04:39.179
♪

00:04:39.179 --> 00:04:40.213
Utopia?

00:04:40.213 --> 00:04:42.716
What's going on?

00:04:42.716 --> 00:04:44.518
Nothing good, Yuma.

00:04:44.518 --> 00:04:46.153
Nothing good!

00:04:46.153 --> 00:04:46.853
Oh, no!

00:04:46.853 --> 00:04:52.893
♪

00:04:55.195 --> 00:04:56.797
Utopia, no!

00:04:56.797 --> 00:05:03.003
♪

00:05:03.003 --> 00:05:04.471
What--what happened?

00:05:04.471 --> 00:05:06.573
Was that my fault?

00:05:06.573 --> 00:05:08.308
For once, no!

00:05:08.308 --> 00:05:11.978
When Giant Hand negated
Utopia's special abilities,

00:05:11.978 --> 00:05:14.214
it also booby trapped Utopia,

00:05:14.214 --> 00:05:16.483
so that if it ever
attacked my Giant Hand,

00:05:16.483 --> 00:05:18.785
it would be destroyed.

00:05:18.785 --> 00:05:19.820
Oh, man!

00:05:19.820 --> 00:05:21.588
This is just the beginning.

00:05:21.588 --> 00:05:23.623
There is so much more to come.

00:05:23.623 --> 00:05:26.793
You see, I have you right
in the palm of my hand.

00:05:26.793 --> 00:05:28.161
Seriously?

00:05:28.161 --> 00:05:30.397
Oh, I would not
lie about this!

00:05:30.397 --> 00:05:31.932
You are going to take damage

00:05:31.932 --> 00:05:34.801
equal to Utopia's
attack points!

00:05:34.801 --> 00:05:36.970
Attack, Giant Hand!

00:05:36.970 --> 00:05:38.271
Not on my watch!

00:05:38.271 --> 00:05:41.141
I activate Shining
Sly's special ability!

00:05:41.141 --> 00:05:43.109
♪

00:05:43.109 --> 00:05:46.913
Now by tributing Gogogo
Golem, Yuma takes no damage!

00:05:46.913 --> 00:05:47.981
Do you get me?

00:05:47.981 --> 00:05:50.584
Or should I hammer
the point home?

00:05:50.584 --> 00:05:54.554
♪

00:05:54.554 --> 00:05:57.324
Looks like your life points
are safe and sound now, Yuma.

00:05:57.324 --> 00:05:59.759
♪

00:05:59.759 --> 00:06:01.328
Not so fast.

00:06:01.328 --> 00:06:03.129
By using one overlay unit,

00:06:03.129 --> 00:06:07.667
Giant Hand stops your
Shining Sly's special ability!

00:06:07.667 --> 00:06:10.904
Go Upper Hand Drillbit Demise!

00:06:10.904 --> 00:06:21.348
♪

00:06:21.348 --> 00:06:23.049
I can't believe this!

00:06:23.049 --> 00:06:25.552
Aww, man!

00:06:25.552 --> 00:06:27.420
And now back to Yuma.

00:06:27.420 --> 00:06:29.489
Before Ray bought
you a little time,

00:06:29.489 --> 00:06:33.193
you were set to take a serious
pounding from my monster,

00:06:33.193 --> 00:06:35.295
Hand Destruction!

00:06:35.295 --> 00:06:37.297
(explosions)

00:06:37.297 --> 00:06:39.299
(yelling)

00:06:39.299 --> 00:06:43.536
♪

00:06:43.536 --> 00:06:44.671
Yuma, no!

00:06:44.671 --> 00:06:48.541
♪

00:06:48.541 --> 00:06:51.611
Each move you make is
worse than the last one!

00:06:51.611 --> 00:06:53.313
I pity you, Yuma.

00:06:53.313 --> 00:06:56.850
Having to make up for your
latest blunder will not be easy.

00:06:56.850 --> 00:06:59.386
♪

00:06:59.386 --> 00:07:01.254
Yuma, I'm so sorry.

00:07:01.254 --> 00:07:02.589
Please forgive me.

00:07:02.589 --> 00:07:03.990
No sweat, I'll handle it.

00:07:03.990 --> 00:07:04.791
You will?

00:07:04.791 --> 00:07:05.859
Yeah.

00:07:05.859 --> 00:07:07.694
I just got to figure out how.

00:07:07.694 --> 00:07:09.029
But it won't be easy.

00:07:09.029 --> 00:07:11.031
If he attacks next
turn, I'm finished.

00:07:11.031 --> 00:07:12.732
I gotta make sure he can't

00:07:12.732 --> 00:07:15.802
and Swords of Burning Light
will make that a reality.

00:07:15.802 --> 00:07:19.072
I activate the spell
Swords of Burning Light!

00:07:19.072 --> 00:07:23.843
♪

00:07:23.843 --> 00:07:26.880
Now with this on my
field, no one can attack.

00:07:26.880 --> 00:07:28.148
I have to watch what I do,

00:07:28.148 --> 00:07:30.150
'cause if I summon a
monster to my field,

00:07:30.150 --> 00:07:32.719
Swords of Burning
Light will be destroyed.

00:07:32.719 --> 00:07:35.422
I gotta play this safe.

00:07:35.422 --> 00:07:37.357
I end my turn.

00:07:37.357 --> 00:07:39.726
And now, I draw!

00:07:39.726 --> 00:07:43.730
I activate the spell
Rank-Up-Magic Barian's Force!

00:07:43.730 --> 00:07:45.966
♪

00:07:45.966 --> 00:07:51.604
This card ranks up my Giant
Hand into a Chaos Xyz Monster.

00:07:51.604 --> 00:07:53.940
Things just got a
whole lot tougher!

00:07:53.940 --> 00:07:57.110
I overlay my Rank 4 Giant Hand!

00:07:57.110 --> 00:08:00.280
♪

00:08:00.280 --> 00:08:03.683
And with this monster, I
rebuild the Overlay Network!

00:08:03.683 --> 00:08:07.220
Go Chaos Xyz Evolution!

00:08:07.220 --> 00:08:11.491
Come forth,
Chaos Number 106,

00:08:11.491 --> 00:08:14.561
Giant Red Hand!

00:08:14.561 --> 00:08:17.297
With the power to
harness this chaotic world,

00:08:17.297 --> 00:08:19.833
its fist will smash the land!

00:08:19.833 --> 00:08:22.435
Its fingers will tear the sky!

00:08:22.435 --> 00:08:29.676
♪

00:08:29.676 --> 00:08:30.810
That's scary!

00:08:30.810 --> 00:08:36.249
♪

00:08:36.249 --> 00:08:38.885
That thing looks ready
to bring some pain our way!

00:08:38.885 --> 00:08:40.987
How right you are!

00:08:40.987 --> 00:08:45.158
I activate Giant Red
Hand's special ability!

00:08:45.158 --> 00:08:47.894
By using one
Chaos Overlay Unit,

00:08:47.894 --> 00:08:51.431
all other face-up cards
lose their effects!

00:08:51.431 --> 00:08:53.867
Heavy Handed Hurricane!

00:08:53.867 --> 00:08:55.935
♪

00:08:55.935 --> 00:08:57.804
My Swords of Burning Light!

00:08:57.804 --> 00:09:01.241
Now, without your Swords
of Burning Light to stop it,

00:09:01.241 --> 00:09:04.711
my Giant Red Hand can
attack you directly!

00:09:04.711 --> 00:09:07.447
-Not good.
-Yuma!

00:09:07.447 --> 00:09:09.249
Onslaught Spiral!

00:09:09.249 --> 00:09:12.485
♪

00:09:12.485 --> 00:09:13.620
Not so fast!

00:09:13.620 --> 00:09:15.455
I activate Shining Stunt!

00:09:15.455 --> 00:09:18.124
By taking half your monster's
attack points as damage,

00:09:18.124 --> 00:09:20.093
this trap stops
your monster's attack

00:09:20.093 --> 00:09:21.861
and ends the battle!

00:09:21.861 --> 00:09:25.465
♪

00:09:25.465 --> 00:09:26.933
So Yuma's safe.

00:09:26.933 --> 00:09:30.503
♪

00:09:30.503 --> 00:09:31.638
Ray, no!

00:09:31.638 --> 00:09:36.476
♪

00:09:36.476 --> 00:09:38.611
Oh no, Ray!

00:09:38.611 --> 00:09:42.215
I just wanted to do
something right for a change.

00:09:42.215 --> 00:09:44.250
♪

00:09:44.250 --> 00:09:48.121
Just wish you hadn't
gotten yourself hurt.

00:09:48.121 --> 00:09:49.689
But getting hurt
is the only way

00:09:49.689 --> 00:09:53.226
that Ray can do anything right!

00:09:53.226 --> 00:09:55.728
I place two cards facedown,

00:09:55.728 --> 00:09:59.766
and then I activate the field
spell Erosion Hand Forest!

00:09:59.766 --> 00:10:00.934
♪

00:10:00.934 --> 00:10:03.203
And it will really grow on you.

00:10:03.203 --> 00:10:08.975
Every time it is my turn, we
all take 1,000 points of damage!

00:10:08.975 --> 00:10:10.410
But that means--

00:10:10.410 --> 00:10:13.646
On my next turn,
I automatically win!

00:10:13.646 --> 00:10:23.623
♪

00:10:26.159 --> 00:10:29.028
Man, I hope Yuma and Ray know
what they're doing in there!

00:10:29.028 --> 00:10:31.131
I've got my fingers
and toes crossed for 'em.

00:10:31.131 --> 00:10:35.602
♪

00:10:35.602 --> 00:10:38.571
Yuma--

00:10:38.571 --> 00:10:40.874
This is it, we only
have one turn left!

00:10:40.874 --> 00:10:42.842
Yuma, listen to me.

00:10:42.842 --> 00:10:44.811
No matter how badly it
looks like I'll get hurt,

00:10:44.811 --> 00:10:46.813
do not bail me out this time.

00:10:46.813 --> 00:10:47.914
You've been a great friend,

00:10:47.914 --> 00:10:50.150
and now I plan to
return the favor.

00:10:50.150 --> 00:10:51.351
But Ray--

00:10:51.351 --> 00:10:53.820
Get ready to hand over
those Numbers, Yuma.

00:10:53.820 --> 00:10:56.456
And Ray, you never should
have messed with Alito!

00:10:56.456 --> 00:10:58.992
Remember that when I
bring you down next turn!

00:10:58.992 --> 00:11:01.227
I wouldn't be so
sure about that!

00:11:01.227 --> 00:11:02.962
Now I draw!

00:11:02.962 --> 00:11:07.367
♪

00:11:07.367 --> 00:11:10.270
And summon my Shining
Rabbit onto the field!

00:11:10.270 --> 00:11:14.707
♪

00:11:14.707 --> 00:11:17.544
Next I'll activate the
spell card Shining Bridge!

00:11:17.544 --> 00:11:21.047
♪

00:11:21.047 --> 00:11:22.649
It allows my Shining Rabbit

00:11:22.649 --> 00:11:24.417
to attack you directly!

00:11:24.417 --> 00:11:26.452
(yelling)

00:11:26.452 --> 00:11:28.388
♪

00:11:28.388 --> 00:11:29.923
And if the attack succeeds,

00:11:29.923 --> 00:11:32.525
I can destroy your
Erosion Hand Forest!

00:11:32.525 --> 00:11:34.027
♪

00:11:34.027 --> 00:11:35.161
That's amazing!

00:11:35.161 --> 00:11:37.130
I didn't know you
had it in ya, Ray!

00:11:37.130 --> 00:11:38.531
I'm full of surprises!

00:11:38.531 --> 00:11:40.133
Hop to it, Rabbit!

00:11:40.133 --> 00:11:43.203
Ha, your monster should
look before it leaps!

00:11:43.203 --> 00:11:46.105
I activate the trap Hand Vice!

00:11:46.105 --> 00:11:49.375
It will smash your
Shining Rabbit in its tracks!

00:11:49.375 --> 00:11:57.884
♪

00:11:57.884 --> 00:12:00.820
And things are going
from bad to worse, Ray.

00:12:00.820 --> 00:12:02.589
You also take damage equal

00:12:02.589 --> 00:12:04.924
to Shining Rabbit's
attack points!

00:12:04.924 --> 00:12:06.593
Oh no--

00:12:06.593 --> 00:12:08.661
That is putting it lightly.

00:12:08.661 --> 00:12:24.143
♪

00:12:24.143 --> 00:12:25.545
What happened?

00:12:25.545 --> 00:12:28.147
I played the trap
card Desperate Guard.

00:12:28.147 --> 00:12:30.817
♪

00:12:30.817 --> 00:12:32.685
Desperate Guard?

00:12:32.685 --> 00:12:35.488
This trap card lets me
pay half of my life points,

00:12:35.488 --> 00:12:37.757
so Ray won't take any damage!

00:12:37.757 --> 00:12:39.225
But why, Yuma?

00:12:39.225 --> 00:12:41.227
(yelling)

00:12:41.227 --> 00:12:45.531
♪

00:12:45.531 --> 00:12:47.567
The more you try
to help each other,

00:12:47.567 --> 00:12:49.135
the more you hurt each other!

00:12:49.135 --> 00:12:50.670
You two are a joke!

00:12:50.670 --> 00:12:51.838
Yuma, how could you?

00:12:51.838 --> 00:12:52.972
Don't you remember I asked you

00:12:52.972 --> 00:12:55.041
not to bail me out anymore!

00:12:55.041 --> 00:12:56.676
Yeah Ray, I know.

00:12:56.676 --> 00:12:58.945
But that's just
not how I roll.

00:12:58.945 --> 00:13:01.214
I'm not the kind of guy who
can just sit back and watch

00:13:01.214 --> 00:13:03.816
while his friends get hurt
and he does nothing at all!

00:13:03.816 --> 00:13:05.652
♪

00:13:05.652 --> 00:13:08.321
I understand.

00:13:08.321 --> 00:13:11.524
Now I draw!

00:13:11.524 --> 00:13:12.759
Go right ahead!

00:13:12.759 --> 00:13:14.761
I have a trap waiting for you.

00:13:14.761 --> 00:13:17.997
I activate Damaging Hand!

00:13:17.997 --> 00:13:21.434
Yuma, since you do not have
any monsters on your field,

00:13:21.434 --> 00:13:23.670
you take 300 points of damage

00:13:23.670 --> 00:13:25.872
for every card in your hand!

00:13:25.872 --> 00:13:29.342
I got three cards, so that
means I'm in big trouble!

00:13:29.342 --> 00:13:30.977
That is right!

00:13:30.977 --> 00:13:33.246
You take 900 points of damage,

00:13:33.246 --> 00:13:37.517
more than enough to wipe out
the rest of your life points!

00:13:37.517 --> 00:13:41.487
♪

00:13:41.487 --> 00:13:42.588
Think again!

00:13:42.588 --> 00:13:46.092
I activate the trap
Shining Reborn!

00:13:46.092 --> 00:13:48.728
I tribute two of my
monsters on my field

00:13:48.728 --> 00:13:51.664
to send Yuma's entire
hand to the graveyard!

00:13:51.664 --> 00:13:56.002
♪

00:13:56.002 --> 00:13:57.470
You know what you have done?

00:13:57.470 --> 00:13:58.838
Blocked your move, that's what!

00:13:58.838 --> 00:14:00.139
If your opponent has no cards,

00:14:00.139 --> 00:14:01.974
Damaging Hand has no effect!

00:14:01.974 --> 00:14:03.609
How dare you!

00:14:03.609 --> 00:14:04.977
Uh, Ray?

00:14:04.977 --> 00:14:06.145
And there's more!

00:14:06.145 --> 00:14:08.014
Shining Rabbit
summons an Xyz Monster

00:14:08.014 --> 00:14:10.917
back from Yuma's graveyard!

00:14:10.917 --> 00:14:13.653
I bring back
Number 39: Utopia!

00:14:13.653 --> 00:14:19.425
♪

00:14:19.425 --> 00:14:22.028
When did this twerp
learn how to duel?

00:14:22.028 --> 00:14:23.696
Now why worry about that?

00:14:23.696 --> 00:14:25.331
You have bigger problems.

00:14:25.331 --> 00:14:27.800
Like Shining Reborn's
last effect.

00:14:27.800 --> 00:14:30.470
I can give a card to Yuma.

00:14:30.470 --> 00:14:34.273
Here, catch!

00:14:34.273 --> 00:14:35.675
No way!

00:14:35.675 --> 00:14:38.378
It's Rank-Up-Magic
Limited Barian's Force!

00:14:38.378 --> 00:14:40.446
♪

00:14:40.446 --> 00:14:41.614
A Barian card?

00:14:41.614 --> 00:14:43.216
How'd you get this?

00:14:43.216 --> 00:14:45.184
I'll explain everything later.

00:14:45.184 --> 00:14:46.686
But first, let's win!

00:14:46.686 --> 00:14:49.222
By using a Barian
card...I don't know.

00:14:49.222 --> 00:14:51.824
Yuma, I need you
to trust me on this.

00:14:51.824 --> 00:14:55.061
Can you do that
for me, for a friend?

00:14:55.061 --> 00:14:56.529
I wanna trust Ray.

00:14:56.529 --> 00:14:57.597
But should I?

00:14:57.597 --> 00:14:59.198
He had a Barian Card?

00:14:59.198 --> 00:15:01.134
These things have been
nothin' but trouble!

00:15:01.134 --> 00:15:03.236
Still I gotta win for Astral!

00:15:03.236 --> 00:15:06.305
And that means there's
only one thing for me to do!

00:15:06.305 --> 00:15:10.109
I'm feeling the flow!

00:15:10.109 --> 00:15:14.414
I activate Rank-Up-Magic
Limited Barian's Force!

00:15:14.414 --> 00:15:17.550
(together)
Time to overlay
Number 39: Utopia!

00:15:17.550 --> 00:15:21.788
♪

00:15:21.788 --> 00:15:25.525
I rebuild the Overlay
Network with Utopia!

00:15:25.525 --> 00:15:27.794
♪

00:15:27.794 --> 00:15:31.230
(together)
Now go Chaos Xyz Evolution!

00:15:31.230 --> 00:15:43.342
♪

00:15:43.342 --> 00:15:47.580
Come on out, Chaos
Number 39: Utopia Ray V!

00:15:47.580 --> 00:16:09.902
♪

00:16:11.637 --> 00:16:18.211
♪

00:16:18.211 --> 00:16:19.078
Whoa!

00:16:19.078 --> 00:16:21.447
Utopia just got
a major upgrade!

00:16:21.447 --> 00:16:22.348
That's right.

00:16:22.348 --> 00:16:24.717
This is your new monster, Yuma.

00:16:24.717 --> 00:16:28.921
Man, Utopia's had a
real big growth spurt!

00:16:28.921 --> 00:16:30.957
That's a good thing, right?

00:16:30.957 --> 00:16:33.826
What, how could they
summon a Chaos Number?

00:16:33.826 --> 00:16:37.296
There is more to these
two than meets the eye!

00:16:37.296 --> 00:16:39.565
-Now, Yuma!
-Yeah!

00:16:39.565 --> 00:16:43.636
I activate Utopia Ray
V's special ability!

00:16:43.636 --> 00:16:47.573
I can use one Chaos Overlay
Unit to destroy your monster!

00:16:47.573 --> 00:16:50.443
♪

00:16:50.443 --> 00:16:52.011
Utopia Ray V,

00:16:52.011 --> 00:16:54.180
destroy Giant Red Hand!

00:16:54.180 --> 00:17:00.152
♪

00:17:00.152 --> 00:17:02.722
Go, spinning
Blades of Destruction!

00:17:02.722 --> 00:17:09.328
♪

00:17:09.328 --> 00:17:13.266
You take damage equal to Giant
Hand Red's attack points, Girag!

00:17:13.266 --> 00:17:15.234
(explosions)

00:17:15.234 --> 00:17:23.609
♪

00:17:23.609 --> 00:17:25.711
Now to finish you off for good!

00:17:25.711 --> 00:17:28.881
Utopia Ray V,
attack Girag directly!

00:17:28.881 --> 00:17:33.486
♪

00:17:33.486 --> 00:17:36.088
Rising sun star slash!

00:17:36.088 --> 00:17:48.868
♪

00:17:48.868 --> 00:17:50.336
Hey, Ray, look.

00:17:50.336 --> 00:17:55.975
♪

00:17:55.975 --> 00:17:57.843
You--

00:17:57.843 --> 00:18:00.713
Ray, how did you
have a Barian Card?

00:18:00.713 --> 00:18:02.315
Just who are you?

00:18:02.315 --> 00:18:04.784
Oh, don't worry
you'll find out.

00:18:04.784 --> 00:18:06.385
Well, eventually.

00:18:06.385 --> 00:18:16.095
♪

00:18:16.095 --> 00:18:17.930
The Sphere's going haywire!

00:18:17.930 --> 00:18:19.799
We beat him.

00:18:19.799 --> 00:18:21.968
That's right,
thanks to you.

00:18:21.968 --> 00:18:24.704
You stood by my side and
trusted me all the way.

00:18:24.704 --> 00:18:27.974
And I realize that may
not have been easy to do.

00:18:27.974 --> 00:18:30.176
You are a true friend.

00:18:30.176 --> 00:18:32.011
Wait, just hang on there, Ray!

00:18:32.011 --> 00:18:34.947
You still gotta tell me
what's up with that Barian card.

00:18:34.947 --> 00:18:37.483
You got some explaining to do!

00:18:37.483 --> 00:18:40.019
I'm with the Barian
Cosmic Crime Unit.

00:18:40.019 --> 00:18:41.153
Hang on, Ray.

00:18:41.153 --> 00:18:42.488
Did you say the B-word?

00:18:42.488 --> 00:18:44.090
Yes I did.

00:18:44.090 --> 00:18:45.458
Does this shock you?

00:18:45.458 --> 00:18:47.793
No, I'm cool.

00:18:47.793 --> 00:18:49.261
So, uh, you mean--

00:18:49.261 --> 00:18:51.597
No way, you're a Barian?

00:18:51.597 --> 00:18:52.698
Shh.

00:18:52.698 --> 00:18:58.471
♪

00:18:58.471 --> 00:18:59.438
Yuma!

00:18:59.438 --> 00:19:00.606
And Ray!

00:19:00.606 --> 00:19:02.274
Hey, you guys won!

00:19:02.274 --> 00:19:04.410
Yeah, all right!

00:19:04.410 --> 00:19:07.179
Well it's all thanks to Yuma.

00:19:07.179 --> 00:19:11.684
I kept making mistakes, but
he pulled us both through!

00:19:11.684 --> 00:19:15.087
No matter how ugly things
got, he never gave up on me.

00:19:15.087 --> 00:19:17.623
Yuma, here.

00:19:17.623 --> 00:19:18.758
Thanks, Tori.

00:19:18.758 --> 00:19:23.929
♪

00:19:23.929 --> 00:19:28.267
Yuma, well done, my friend.

00:19:28.267 --> 00:19:31.370
♪

00:19:31.370 --> 00:19:33.939
(Yuma)
So, you've known about
Astral this whole time?

00:19:33.939 --> 00:19:37.076
(Ray)
I've been able to see him since
I first arrived in your world

00:19:37.076 --> 00:19:38.477
and began my mission.

00:19:38.477 --> 00:19:39.712
What mission?

00:19:39.712 --> 00:19:42.148
To find Barian criminals
hiding among you.

00:19:42.148 --> 00:19:43.783
♪

00:19:43.783 --> 00:19:46.919
So on Barian World there's
good guys and bad guys?

00:19:46.919 --> 00:19:48.120
Correct, Yuma.

00:19:48.120 --> 00:19:50.423
Barian World isn't
an evil place,

00:19:50.423 --> 00:19:53.826
but some step out of line.

00:19:53.826 --> 00:19:55.227
That's the truth.

00:19:55.227 --> 00:19:58.698
And now that you know,
let's work together.

00:19:58.698 --> 00:19:59.832
You serious?

00:19:59.832 --> 00:20:01.333
Awesome!

00:20:01.333 --> 00:20:03.202
When Astral finds out
there's a Barian good guy

00:20:03.202 --> 00:20:05.438
workin' to nab the
evil ones, he'll flip!

00:20:05.438 --> 00:20:06.706
He cannot find out.

00:20:06.706 --> 00:20:08.207
This has to be our secret.

00:20:08.207 --> 00:20:09.475
But how come?

00:20:09.475 --> 00:20:11.310
I have to stay undercover.

00:20:11.310 --> 00:20:13.179
If Astral were to
know of my existence,

00:20:13.179 --> 00:20:15.881
he would be in even greater
danger than he is now.

00:20:15.881 --> 00:20:18.417
The fewer people that
know about me the better.

00:20:18.417 --> 00:20:20.753
I do not want anyone
else learning the truth.

00:20:20.753 --> 00:20:22.088
Can I trust you, as a friend,

00:20:22.088 --> 00:20:23.689
to keep my secret?

00:20:23.689 --> 00:20:25.458
Of course, totally!

00:20:25.458 --> 00:20:28.894
Okay, then starting today,
you're my new sidekick!

00:20:28.894 --> 00:20:32.498
I always thought you had the
makings of a great underling!

00:20:32.498 --> 00:20:34.033
That sounds awesome to me.

00:20:34.033 --> 00:20:35.768
I won't let you down, Ray!

00:20:35.768 --> 00:20:39.405
Yeah!

00:20:39.405 --> 00:20:41.507
Though I can't say
the same for myself!

00:20:41.507 --> 00:20:43.943
♪

